I met with my oncologist today and he doesn’t sugar coat anything, which I appreciate. On the positive side he still feels I haven’t progressed but is willing to order another PET Scan to see if we can get more clarity on why my CA-125 is increasing. But he was very clear that my can is incurable and that there a NO drugs approved to treat it. So whatever we do will be a clinical trial with an n of 1. I feel good so I’m still hopeful I can remain progression free for a good while longer. I don’t live in the future, I try to stay in the present. Today I feel good but a little sad.
